# ============================================================================
# N2KShield .gitignore
# ============================================================================
# This file prevents large data files and sensitive information from being
# pushed to GitHub. Here's what we DON'T push and WHY:
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# 1. NMEA2000 RAW DATA - DO NOT PUSH!
# ============================================================================
# WHY: ~3 million frames = hundreds of MB, too large for GitHub
# WHY: May contain sensitive boat navigation data (GPS positions, routes)
# WHY: Can be regenerated from original source if needed

NMEA2000/
Frame*.txt
**/Frame*.txt

# ============================================================================
# 2. PROCESSED DATA FILES - DO NOT PUSH!
# ============================================================================
# WHY: Large files generated from raw data
# WHY: Can be regenerated by running preprocessing scripts
# WHY: Takes up repository space unnecessarily

data/raw/
data/decoded/
data/preprocessed/
data/processed/

# Specific data file patterns
*.csv
*.npy
*.npz
*.hdf5
*.h5  # Note: .h5 could be models OR data, see models section below
*.parquet
*.feather

# ============================================================================
# 3. TRAINED MODELS - CONDITIONAL (Large files)
# ============================================================================
# WHY: Model weights can be 10-100+ MB each
# WHY: Should be stored in Git LFS or separate model registry
# WHY: Can be retrained from code + data
# 
# KEEP: Model architecture code (Python files)
# IGNORE: Saved model weights

models/checkpoints/
models/saved/
models/*.h5
models/*.hdf5
models/*.pt
models/*.pth
models/*.ckpt
models/*.pb
*.keras
*.weights.h5

# ============================================================================
# 4. RESULTS & OUTPUTS - CONDITIONAL
# ============================================================================
# WHY: Generated outputs that can be reproduced
# KEEP: Small result summaries (< 1MB)
# IGNORE: Large result files, plots, logs

results/large/
results/experiments/
logs/
outputs/
*.log

# Large visualization files (keep small PNGs for documentation)
results/**/*.png
results/**/*.jpg
results/**/*.pdf
!results/final/*.png  # Exception: keep final publication figures

# ============================================================================
# 5. SCALERS & PREPROCESSING ARTIFACTS
# ============================================================================
# WHY: Generated during preprocessing, can be recreated
# WHY: Specific to training data, may change

data/scalers/
*.pkl
*.pickle
*.joblib
scaler*.json

# ============================================================================
# 6. TEMPORARY & CACHE FILES
# ============================================================================
# WHY: System-generated, not part of source code

# Python cache
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg
MANIFEST

# Jupyter Notebook checkpoints
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*/.ipynb_checkpoints/*

# Virtual environments
venv/
env/
ENV/
env.bak/
venv.bak/
.venv/

# IDE specific files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ============================================================================
# 7. CREDENTIALS & SECRETS - CRITICAL!
# ============================================================================
# WHY: Security! Never push passwords, API keys, tokens
# WHY: Protects access to servers, databases, services

.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
secrets.yaml
credentials.json
*.key
*.pem
ssh_config
**/secrets/

# ============================================================================
# 8. SYSTEM & OS FILES
# ============================================================================

# Linux
*~
.directory

# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Windows
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# ============================================================================
# 9. LARGE BINARY FILES
# ============================================================================
# WHY: GitHub has 100MB file limit, large files cause push failures

*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.rar
*.7z
*.iso

# ============================================================================
# 10. REFERENCE MATERIALS (if large)
# ============================================================================
# KEEP: Small PDFs with reference papers
# IGNORE: Large datasets or documentation archives

papers/datasets/
papers/large/

# ============================================================================
# WHAT WE **DO** PUSH TO GITHUB:
# ============================================================================
# ✅ All Python source code (.py files)
# ✅ Configuration files (.yaml, .json - without secrets)
# ✅ This plan document (N2KSHIELD_STEP_BY_STEP_PLAN.md)
# ✅ README.md and documentation
# ✅ Requirements.txt (Python dependencies)
# ✅ Small reference papers (CANShield PDF)
# ✅ Scripts and utilities
# ✅ Test files
# ✅ Small example data (if < 1MB)
# ✅ Final publication figures (selective)
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# EXCEPTIONS (Force include specific files if needed)
# ============================================================================
# Use ! to force include files that would otherwise be ignored
# Example:
# !data/examples/small_sample.csv  # Small example dataset OK to push
# !models/architecture_diagram.png  # Documentation image OK to push
# ============================================================================

# Force include important documentation images
!docs/**/*.png
!docs/**/*.jpg
!README_images/*.png

# ============================================================================
# END OF .gitignore
# ============================================================================
# Total protection: ~3GB of data files will NOT be pushed to GitHub
# Only source code, configs, and docs will be in repository
# This keeps repo clean, fast, and under GitHub size limits
# ============================================================================
